description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We have an exciting opportunity to recruit a dynamic and highly motivated person to work as a care co-ordinator alongside our West Somerset PCN Multi-Disciplinary Team. This non-clinical role involves proactively identifying and working with people, including the frail/elderly and those with long-term conditions, to provide coordination and navigation of care and support across health and care services, including care homes.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;You would work closely with the GP practice teams to manage a caseload of patients, acting as a central point of contact to ensure appropriate support is made available to them and their carers; supporting them to understand and manage their condition and ensuring their changing needs are addressed. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to join an established multi-disciplinary team to work collectively to facilitate quality care to a wide range of people in West Somerset. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post is fortwo whole time equivalent, and we welcome applications for both full or part-time employment.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please open the job description/person specification for a comprehensive overview of the role.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;For more information contact Kerry Morgan, West Somerset PCN Manager: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;kerry.morgan2@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
